message.body: Good luck today!!!!
Thanks!
I think that Estée Lauder stuff is making me breakout/turn red! I'm not irritated, but my face is red and blotchy
I could probably return it to sephora, right. Although I don't have a receipt.
Awwww
I know. I don't know...should I keep at it or just return it? I want it to work
Lol try it for another day or 2
Yeah. Maybe instead of every night I can do every other night and then gradually increase too. Why does my face suck?!
Lol idk..
So my questions for the interview: do I need any certifications or clearances, how much traveling would be involved, what's a typical schedule for a student, what do you expect from students... Good?
How much traveling for what?
Clinical a
clinicals*
I didn't know if they used other places too lol
Ohh. Okay. I assumed it would be mainly at jefferson.
True. Yeah. Sounds good to me.
Ahhh good luck good luck good luck!
Ahh I'm so scared!
Don't be!!!! I'm sure it'll be fine! Don't psych yourself out. You're well prepared and from what I've read online, it's very laid back not scary!
It's a group interview. Lord Jesus help us all. Lol there are 4 other people here to interview with me
What?! How the heck is that going to work?
I don't understand what is happening to my face! I didn't put anything on and I woke up with dry patches everywhere including my eyelid! And I'm breaking out on my cheeks.
Omg that's awful! Stop the Estée Lauder stuff. Holy crap.
I didn't use it yesterday.
But it might just be your face getting worse from earlier..
Did you use my lush moisturizer?
Yes I did! I don't understand!
This morning?
I used it on the dry patch and it burned and then turned redder.
Okay...not burned...tingled.
That's crazy...
I know. I was debating just staying home because my face is a hot mess.
Did you try using my thingamabobber?
No. I didn't have time.
What time are you done today?
I'll probably get to market around 5 or 530.
That suxjs
I know! I'm debating just going to my lab and sulking at the library. Haha
Hahaha
Ughhhh! I guess it could also be because of my period.
Maybe.. That's crazy though
I know! I usually break out before my period but this be ridiculous. I'm hoping that it slowly goes away.
